# Hooks registry

This machine's hook ledger. The claude-global-memory scaffold installs exactly
one hook by default — the **memory-loader**, the cross-project memory layer's
load mechanism (see `HOOKS.md`, "The load-bearing exception") — and touches
`settings.json` only for its two registrations. Bootstrap manages that hook's
row below (adds it on install, removes it on uninstall); every other row
tracks a hook you added yourself and is never touched.

A hook is integration plumbing, governed like code, not a memory entry. Before
adding a guardrail hook it must clear the admission policy in
[`HOOKS.md`](https://github.com/MHouse/claude-global-memory/blob/main/HOOKS.md)
(all six points + a postmortem). Adding a hook is a 3-step manual recipe
(script + `settings.json` block + a row below); removing one reverses all three.
The full recipe lives in `HOOKS.md`.

